# Pong-RN Game Improvement Plan

Investigation and implementation roadmap. **Priority: HUD board — centered horizontally in both orientations.** Landscape court layout stays as-is; scoreboard top-center on court. Portrait gets a dedicated top HUD (score centered in bar) + smaller play board. Free rotation on intro/win screens; **locked during active play**.

### Scoreboard rule (both orientations)

- Score row (`AI | score : score | You`) is **horizontally centered** always
- **Landscape:** scoreboard **top-center** on court (`alignItems: 'center'`, `justifyContent: 'flex-start'`)
- **Portrait:** scoreboard centered within the top HUD bar (not left-aligned)

### Gameplay rule (orientation-specific axes)

| | **Landscape** | **Portrait** |
|---|---------------|--------------|
| AI paddle | Left — moves vertically | Top — moves horizontally |
| Player paddle | Right — drag vertically | Bottom — drag horizontally |
| Ball | Moves horizontally; bounces top/bottom walls | Moves vertically; bounces left/right walls |
| Scoring | Ball exits left (you score) / right (AI scores) | Ball exits top (you score) / bottom (AI scores) |
| Court aspect | Full flex court, 5% side margins | Fixed 9:16 tall court below HUD (`COURT_ASPECT_RATIO_PORTRAIT`) |

### Powerup legend (colored court icons)

Powerups spawn on court during play (~every 8s, max 5, 6s lifetime). Each is a **colored circle with a white first-letter label** and a **buff / debuff / mystery ring** (blue / red / gold). The collector is whichever side owns that half of the court when the ball hits or you tap the orb — **AI** (left/top) or **You** (right/bottom).

**16 types** in `POWERUP_LABELS` / `POWERUP_COLORS` (`src/constants/game.ts`). Spawn weights in `pickSpawnPowerup()` (`src/utils/powerups.ts`) — Easy biases grow/ally when losing; Hard biases enemy/mystery/shrink.

| Tier | Labels | Summary |
|------|--------|---------|
| Paddle | **G S F T N K** | Grow, Shrink, Fast, Thick, Narrow, Sticky |
| Ball | **B C M R** | Boost, Curve, Multi (2-ball), Reverse |
| Court | **O X Z** | Temp stone, Clear stone, Disable center slow |
| Mind-game | **A E ?** | Ally buff, Enemy debuff (opponent), Mystery roll |

**HUD chips** beside AI / You scores show active effects (`POWERUP_HUD_LABELS`, e.g. `G↑`, `B»`, `E↓`). Component: `src/components/Powerup.tsx` (orb pulse in last 2s). Collector rules + full tier tables in **Phase8** below.

### Serve rule

| Rule | Behavior |
|------|----------|
| **Opening serve** | **Player (You)** always serves first — `OPENING_SERVE_SIDE` / `PLAYER_SERVE_SIDE` = `0` in `ballLaunch.ts` |
| **After a point** | Scorer serves — `serveSideAfterScore()` (player = side `0`, AI = side `1`) |
| **Attach delay** | Ball sticks to serving paddle **3 s** (1 s after AI scores), then auto-launches |
| **Tap to serve** | On **player serve only** (`ballAttachSide === 0`): quick tap on court launches early (`Gesture.Tap` + `tryLaunchPlayerServe`) |
| **Launch angle** | Random cross-court component + random offset along paddle edge; velocity computed on **JS thread** (`randomLaunchVelocity`, `releaseAttachedBall`) |

### Orientation rule

| Screen state | Rotation |
|--------------|----------|
| Intro (`StartOverlay`) | Free — portrait ↔ landscape |
| Win (`WinOverlay`) | Free |
| Active play (`gameStarted && !winner`) | **Locked** to orientation at game start |
| Pause overlay | Locked (still in active match) |

Mid-game live relayout was removed after device QA showed broken paddle positions and missing balls. `expo-screen-orientation` locks the device during play; a `RotationLockedBanner` appears (with brief auto-pause) if the player physically rotates the device.

### Court color rule

| Mode | Behavior |
|------|----------|
| **Classic** (default) | `rgb(43,75,53)` — original green playboard |
| **Random** | Picks one color from `RANDOM_COURT_COLORS` in `hud.ts` |

**Random palette:** black, navy, purple, burgundy, teal, charcoal (`#000000`, `#1C2841`, `#3B1F5E`, `#4A1F2E`, `#1A3D3D`, `#2D3748`).

- Toggle on **intro only** (`StartOverlay` — **Board** row: Classic vs Random)
- State: `courtColorMode` + `courtBackgroundColor` in `GameScreen`; `pickRandomCourtColor()` in `hud.ts`
- **Random** rolls on intro select, **Start Game**, and **Play Again** (new color each match)
- **Classic** always uses green; not changeable mid-match or on win overlay

